# Empire — project / workspace folder naming (all nodes)

## Pattern (mandatory for new multi-node-safe roots)

```
Project_<ProjectName>_<NODE>
```

| Part | Meaning | Examples |
|------|---------|----------|
| **Prefix** | Fixed | `Project` |
| **Middle** | Descriptive project name (may contain underscores) | `LAN_Connections_Nodes`, `Openclaw_Gateway`, `EmailAI` |
| **Suffix** | **Node id** — where this folder primarily lives | `HP`, `AI_X1`, future `MINI_PC`, … |

**Examples**

- HP: `C:\Empire\Project_LAN_Connections_Nodes_HP`
- AI_X1: `C:\Empire_AI_X1\Project_LAN_Connections_Nodes_AI_X1`

**Legacy folders** (no `Project_` prefix) may remain until migrated; **new** scaffolds use this pattern.

## Child `generated` (Empire children under `C:\Empire`)

- Use **`generated_Project_<ProjectName>_<NODE>\`** matching the **exact** project folder basename, e.g. `generated_Project_LAN_Connections_Nodes_HP\`.  
- See `core-generated-child-canonical.mdc` and `core-empire-workspace-rename-relocate-discipline.mdc`.

## Agent execution (hands-free / eyes-free)

- **When HP can run tools** (disk, shell, git, `Scripts\`, SMB up): the **agent creates/renames folders**, updates `AGENTS.md` / `README.md`, runs **`Sync_Discovered_Cursor_Paths.py`**, and commits/pushes per doctrine — **do not** push routine “postman copy-paste” steps to VMS for work the agent can do.
- **Postman-style relay** (VMS carries a message to another machine **without** automation): **only** when **HP ↔ worker** link is actually down (no SMB, no git, no node_bus reach) **or** a human-only gate (credentials UI, physical) blocks the agent. If unsure, try agent-side steps first; one short “blocked: X” line if truly stuck.

